      • addSource

        public <T extends TypedTimedAnnotatableSourcedBE> void addSource(T entity,
                                                                 DataSourceInstance source)
        Adds a new source to the provided entity.
        Note that the source MUST be unique for the entity. No other entity can be associated with this particular source. If you want to related multiple DiscourseDB entities with the same source entity, disambiguate the source with the descriptor to make each source unique. e.g. to map a source post identified by its id to a DiscourseDB contribution and a DiscourseDB content, specify the source descriptors like this: contribution#post.id and content#post.id. Ideally, the source descriptors should be defined in a source mapping file. See the edx and prosolo converters for examples.
        Parameters:
        entity - the entity to add a new source to
        source - the source to add to the entity
